More information about these examples can be found from my blog post:
http://tunkkaus.blogspot.fi/

----

This example contains Eclise projects for Grails remote EJB integration
by using JBoss AS 7.1 Java application container.

In order to run these examples, you must have Eclipse/STS/GGTS installed
together with Grails 2.0.4 (newer versions may work also). You must also 
have JBoss AS 7.1.1.Final installed and cofigured to your Eclipse with JBoss
tools. 

JBoss AS and JBoss Tools can be found from:
http://www.jboss.org/jbossas/downloads/  (7.1.1.Final)
http://www.jboss.org/tools

----

These examples have been created by using following sites as a reference:
https://docs.jboss.org/author/display/AS71/Remote+EJB+invocations+via+JNDI+-+EJB+client+API+or+remote-naming+project
http://www.mastertheboss.com/jboss-as-7/jboss-as-7-remote-ejb-client-tutorial

